<span id="freeTextContainer7344561845833923850">This is really a brilliant idea for a collection, and the execution is fantastic. If you follow long-form fantasy at all, you&apos;ll probably at least recognize all of these authors, and each story is a pretty good capsule of the author&apos;s style and world. I&apos;ve found that my reaction to the story maps pretty closely to my reaction to the series as a whole, and so this was a great way to encounter authors I hadn&apos;t yet read (Terry Pratchett, most notably - the Granny Weatherwax story is perfect and a p</span>
  <span id="freeText7344561845833923850" style="display:none">This is really a brilliant idea for a collection, and the execution is fantastic. If you follow long-form fantasy at all, you'll probably at least recognize all of these authors, and each story is a pretty good capsule of the author's style and world. I've found that my reaction to the story maps pretty closely to my reaction to the series as a whole, and so this was a great way to encounter authors I hadn't yet read (Terry Pratchett, most notably - the Granny Weatherwax story is perfect and a perfect introduction to the milieu.)<br /><br />(Note - I read this when it came out, lo these many years ago (and quite a few times since,) so this is a review based on a reread.)</span>
