<span id="freeTextContainer8671700544857338869">I bought this book for <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/7155596.George_R__R__Martin' title='George R. R. Martin' rel='nofollow noopener'>George R. R. Martin</a>&apos;s first Hedge Knight story, which is excellent. It also has stories set in <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/26.Anne_McCaffrey' title='Anne McCaffrey' rel='nofollow noopener'>Anne McCaffrey</a>&apos;s Pern and <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/4338.Robert_Silverberg' title='Robert Silverberg' rel='nofollow noopener'>Robert Silverberg</a>&apos;s Majipoor, as well as a number of other popular fantasy worlds. If I remember correctly, the theme is encompassed by the title, and all of the stories take place in those worlds&apos; early histories.</span>
